						<summary>

						<p>On a broken slab set up near the Āñjanēyasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>Achyuta, 1530 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1449 Vikṛiti, Jyēshṭha śu. 5, Tuesday.</hi> The date is irregular. If Śaka 1449 is a mistake for Śaka 1452, Vikṛiti, the details regularly correspond to <hi rend="bold">1530 A.D., May 31.</hi></p>						

						<p>This fragmentary inscription seems to refer to some grant made for the merit of Ayaparasaya.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
